<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2000-08-08.3.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-00/wa0808.htm#8757">Influenza</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2000-08-08.3.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80165" speakername="Christine Grahame (South of Scotland) (SNP)" spid="S1W-8757" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-00/wa0808.htm#8757">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive, further to the answer to question S1W-8354 by Susan Deacon on 13 July 2000, what criteria were applied to arrive at the 60% target for immunisation of the over 65 age group from the flu virus this year.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2000-08-08.3.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80146" speakername="Susan Deacon" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-00/wa0808.htm#8757">

  <p>60% was agreed with representatives of the BMA in Scotland as a Scotland-wide target which is regarded as both achievable and beneficial. <br /></p>

</reply>
